director of hip, violent and overly clever crime thrillers. This is
what happened to Quentin Tarantino. And, a little later, what
happened to the 32-year-old Singer. (Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TV-GLENN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ From Friendship to Discovery, John
Glenn has been an American hero for more than three decades.
Television was there to beam his first space journey home to us,
and it will be there to record his last. (Holloway, Austin
American-Statesman). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TV-SLAVERY _ AUSTIN, Texas _ How did a nation based on the
concept of liberty and justice for all come to justify the
existence of slavery? This mysterious paradox has puzzled and
troubled us for generations. PBS's new 6-hour documentary series
``Africans in America: America's Journey Through Slavery'' explores
this difficult topic through innovative historical research,
personal stories and superb filmmaking. The result is compelling
television that peels back the layers of America's ongoing struggle
with racism. (Holloway, Austin American-Statesman). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-MORMONS _ ATLANTA _ With the recent establishment of a
regional office here, Atlanta became the only center of Mormon
hierarchy in North America outside Salt Lake City. We look at the
new officials and at the growth in the Southeast that caused the
Presidency to send them here. (White, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-GOSPEL _ It's no secret that contemporary gospel music
has grown in popularity. But at what price? Many traditional gospel
performers _ Shirely Ceaser and The Mighty Clouds of Joy _ are
worried that there brand of gospel music is doomed, a victim of the
Hip Hop and R&AMP;B sounds of a new generation of singers. We take a
look the Gospel music scene, profile some of the biggest players
and try to figure out the direction its headed. (Blake, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   HOME &AMP; GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   PAINT _ You know about coordinating wardrobe colors. But have
you ever thought about what your house is wearing? By coordinating
exterior paint color with landscape plants you can enhance your
home's ``curb appeal,'' as real estate agents call it, by making it
more inviting. It can be as simple as complementing a red front
door with red geraniums near the steps. Or you can think of the
total picture, blending architectural styles with period plants _
roses and old-fashioned annuals planted against a Victorian
cottage, red Japanese maples and ferns to accent a contemporay
home. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS and
LAYOUT
</P>
