   PAINT-TIPS _ Tips on selecting the right color paint for your
home's exterior. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 6-8.
</P>
<P>
   LEEMAY-COLUMN _ Lee ponders the beauty of pregnant onions -- a
type of houseplant -- and other beauties of nature. The plant gets
it name by producing little offsets about the size of peas under
the skin of the mother bulb that sits above the soil. Each baby can
sprout and become a mother when it touches dirt. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
