 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE FEATURES BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These feature stories for release for Saturday, October 17,
1998, are moving today to clients of the New York Times News
Service.
</P>
<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, sports, business and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the category they're listed under. Stories
moving to duplicate categories are marked. All stories have moved
except those with an ETA.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   DECADE17-COX_WASHINGTON _ How about the ``Naughties?''
</P>
<P>
   Or is it ``Noughties?'' Spelling is only one complication of the
coming linguistic crisis: What will we call the next decade?
</P>
<P>
   ``Uh, that's a good question,'' said Gerald Celente, director of
the Trends Research Institute and a futurist paid to ponder such
imponderables. (DART, Cox Washington Bureau). MOVED
</P>
