<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Gardening and star gazing among topics of new books
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ These books by writers at The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution were recently published:
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Backroad Buffets &AMP; Country Cafes: A Southern Guide to
Meat-And-Threes &AMP; Down-Home Dining'' by Don O'Briant. John F. Blair
Publishing. $13.95 paperback. Guidebook covers more than 200
eateries in 20 states, featuring short essays on their favorites
from Southerners such as John Berendt, Roy Blount Jr., Jan Karon,
Larry Brown and Lee Smith.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Gardening Life'' by Lee May. Longstreet Press. $20. A
collection of essays from the Journal-Constitution gardening
columnist.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Star Gazing: Movies and Astrology'' by Eleanor Ringel.
Longstreet Press. $12.95 paperback. Readers can learn which movies
they are most likely to enjoy based on their astrological signs,
which stars share their signs, which movies were released under
which signs, and other trivia from the Journal-Constitution's
longtime movie critic.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
