A1032 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LEWINSKY-SYMPATHY-HNS     10-16 0654
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEWINSKY-SYMPATHY-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SYMPATHY FOR LEWINSKYS OF THE WORLD 
</HEADLINE>
   Commentary  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By EVAN RAIL  
 c.1998 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Following the brouhaha over the White House
sexcapades, I've spent some time deciding who has earned my
sympathy. It's not Monica; she brought this on herself. For the
same reason, it isn't President Clinton. Hillary Rodham Clinton
made a conscious decision to marry the man, and since I still sort
of believe in both freewill and karma, she's out.
</P>
<P>
   The two people I came up with were Chelsea Clinton and Monica's
father, Bernard.
</P>
<P>
   I'm afraid Chelsea may be out of the running, however. For one
thing, she has sympathy coming in from all sides. She's young,
attractive, and the pity is all too obvious. Furthermore, Chelsea
has many years ahead of her, affording her the opportunity to be
judged upon the actions of her own life. Failing that, if Chelsea
were to marry, she could choose to drift into the relative
anonymity of her husband's surname.
</P>
<P>
   This is not the case for Bernard Lewinsky. Not only is he older,
but he's also facing the likelihood that his name will become
synonymous with a couple of different sexual acts. I'm sure that at
some time this man is going to hear the expression ``pull a
Lewinsky'' or ``got a Lewinsky,'' and boy, is he going to blush.
And every time he writes a check or goes through U.S. Customs,
someone's going to raise an eyebrow.
</P>
<P>
   The same for all the Lewinskys and Lewinskis in this country,
most of whom are not directly related to Monica. All I can think
is: Man, what a bummer.
</P>
<P>
   For so many people.
</P>
<P>
   My last name is Rail, ``liar'' spelled backwards, which is kind
of cute, I guess. It at least makes for an innocuous icebreaker. A
rail is a kind of bird found in marshes and wetlands. Compared to
having something like Ramsbottom or Assman for a name, it's not
bad. Aside from my father, a poet, the only notorious Rail I know
of is Jack Rail, a distant uncle, who was a cattle rustler and folk
hero back in Oklahoma. They wrote songs about him.
</P>
<P>
   By way of comparison, contrast the various connotations of your
own last name with those of the future dictionary entry of
``LEWINSKY (loo-in-skee) v. and n.''
</P>
<P>
   I decided to contact some of the objects of my sympathy, the
Lewinskys and Lewinskis of the world. I did a quick search and sent
e-mail messages explaining that I was a writer, and that I wanted
to know how the developments in Washington had affected their
lives, considering their last names. For what it was worth, I even
promised not to identify them.
</P>
<P>
   What I expected was that they had thought about changing their
name to Lewis or Levin, or to some appellation equally discreet. I
expected complaints. The weird thing was that none of the
recipients responded. I guess they're not dealing with the negative
connotations very well.
</P>
<P>
   Come to think of it, ``rail'' is slang for a line of cocaine,
which isn't necessarily negative or positive, although it does have
a meaning other than the little marsh bird who gave his name to my
tribe. There is a slight chance that people have heard my name and
envisioned an Escobar-esque figure, with illegal narcotics and
firearms piled on my desk like Al Pacino in ``Scarface.''
</P>
<P>
   Oh yes, my heart goes out to them, the Lewinskys and Lewinskis
of the world. Anyone who knows that one day he might hear his name
in the context of ``the boss (LAST NAME)ed another intern,'' gets
my sympathy. These are people who can't have something as common as
a cigar come up in conversation without an awkward silence _ simply
because of their name. Men and women, innocents all, whose surname
has come to mean something other than who they are, or what they
were, before this whole thing started.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Evan Rail is a free-lance writer in San Francisco. He has poems
forthcoming in ``Coracle.'')
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
