rate cut late Thursday. At midday Friday, the Dow industrial
average was up 97 points, the Nasdaq index was up 7. Elsewhere,
prices rose 2.2 percent in Tokyo and 9 percent in Hong Kong. They
were up 1.8 percent in Frankfurt and 2.1 percent in London, and
they were little changed in Brazil and Mexico. On the American debt
market, the long bond was off 19/32 point at midday, with the yield
at 5.01 percent. The dollar stood at 116 yen, down from 116.75 yen
on Thursday.
