<SLUG> BC-CHRISROCK-BOOK-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHRIS ROCK MUCH FUNNIER IN PERSON THAN IN PRINT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TIM ROGERS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Anyone who has ever tried to do a Chris Rock bit for a friend
knows that it's impossible. Especially anyone who has attempted to
tell a Chris Rock joke and who happens to be white. Because you
can't tell a Rock joke without copping that voice.
</P>
<P>
   Say these words out loud: ``How much for a rib?''
</P>
<P>
   See?
</P>
<P>
   White people can do Chris Rock's jokes, but they can't do Chris
Rock. And, really, black people can't do him, either. He has what
they call, in street lingo, that je ne sais quoi.
</P>
<P>
   And that's what makes his new book, ``Rock This!'' (Hyperion,
$6.99), merely funny _ not hysterical, like Rock. Much of the book
is just stand-up written down (with the help of David Rensin). If
you've seen Rock's routine, then you'll recognize much of the book.
For example:
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   I also like Clinton because he really needs the job. He needs
the money. Why? Cinton's got real problems. He doesn't have
president problems. He's got real problems just like you and me.
</P>
<P>
   He's running out of money.
</P>
<P>
   His wife's a pain ...
</P>
<P>
   All of his friends are going to jail.
</P>
<P>
   I can relate to Clinton. I know Clinton. I am Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   As long as we're at it, here's more:
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Everyone lies in a relationship. Everyone has secrets. We can't
go into all of them here, but for men, it's that most have some
porno hidden in their house.
</P>
<P>
   You know it's true. I can feel your tension already. You're
squeezing the pages together really hard. ...
</P>
<P>
   When men hide their porno stuff, they really hide it. A man
becomes Batman. It's not behind the speaker, not behind the
dresser, not under the couch. You pull at a book on the bookcase,
the whole (expletive deleted) wall slides to the left, and you
descend two flights of stairs into The Porno Pit.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Believe me, it's difficult to find funny excerpts in this book
that don't include ``adult themes'' and ``potty-mouth language.''
For more reasons than one, then, ``Rock This!'' makes for perfect
bathroom reading. It's a poor substitute for the real thing, but
it's still worth a laugh.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
