<HEADLINE>
AT A GLANCE: 1999 LEXUS LX 470 SPORT-UTILITY WAGON
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Package: Full-size, four-door, eight-passenger, V-8 powered,
full-time four-wheel-drive, luxury sport-utility wagon, an all-new
replacement for the LX 450.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: Power has increased from the previous model, thanks
to an upgrade from an inline six-cylinder to a high-torque V-8
engine; excellent ride and handling on and off the road; superb
luxury in a massive people-mover.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: Off-road performance isn't as good as with the LX
450; the front and rear locking differentials are no longer
available; only a limited-slip rear differential is offered.
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: Range Rover, Lincoln Navigator.
</P>
<P>
   EPA fuel economy: 13 miles per gallon city, 16 highway.
</P>
<P>
   Base price: $54,950 plus $495 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   Price as tested: $57,701, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A-plus.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
