<P>
   DRAW-LIMBAUGH _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ A guy named John
Stevens, who wanders the sidewalks and draws people's portraits in
downtown WPB, reportedly goes to trial today for insulting Marta
Limbaugh, we're told by a tipster. Caller says Stevens got in
trouble while doing a portrait of Rush's wife outside My Martini
restaurant. Limbaugh reportedly offered Stevens a job, and instead,
Stevens insulted her, saying he wasn't willing to kiss her ass for
a living. As a result, the manager at My Martini called the cops,
and supposedly, Stevens was charged with public profanity and
something else. Stevens is representing himself. (Stapleton, Palm
Beach Post). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
