challenger Garry Mauro square off in the only debate of the
campaign. Developing from 8 p.m. CDT debate in El Paso. Ends at 9
p.m. CDT. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   ROAD-SIGNS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ No, it's not your
imagination: The print on those new Interstate 95 signs really IS
bigger than before. State transportation folks decided a couple of
years ago that as signs were replaced, they'd include larger
letters, since we've got so many older drivers. (McGinness, Palm
