<P>
   LAKE CITY, Col. _ To someone from Texas more accustomed to
cowboy boots than hip boots, fly-fishing seemed an exotic sport
requiring the dexterity of a gymnast and the bank account of a
Rockefeller. Over the years, I've learned it simply ain't that
tough, or expensive. It's still exotic, and the scenery is as
breathtaking as the water is cold. All you need is a fly rod, a
handful of flies, waders and a cold, clear river _ just like the
ones in Colorado. By RUSTY HALL. Story has moved in ``t'' travel
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
