<P>
   TRAIN TRIP-ROCKIES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COLORADO and NEW MEXICO _ I like the way our vacation pictures
turned out. There's Patrick, my 7-year-old son, smiling out the
window of our passenger car as the vintage steam engine chugs along
in the background. Next picture: Patrick again, in the open flat
car at the end of the train, grinning up at the camera as rails
disappear into the mountains behind him. Next: Black clouds of
smoke billowing from two locomotives as they climb through the
aspens; then the deep, craggy face of Toltec Gorge as seen from
hundreds of feet above, on the thin ribbon of rail. It had been a
day for my boy, who is a train nut. But the photos remind of the
rustling aspens, the mountains all around, the deep gorges,
trestles over mountain streams, inky tunnels, a doe on the hill,
the brisk air. If this jaunt through the Rocky Mountains on the
Cumbres and Toltec Scenic Railroad was kid stuff, then I was glad
to be a boy again, too. By TIM MADIGAN. Story has moved in ``t''
travel category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
