rescue of the nation's teetering banking system Friday, in a
critical bid to get money flowing through the crippled and
cash-strapped economy. The legislation has been the focus of
worldwide attention as officials from Asia to America look to Japan
to help avert a global recession. By Sheryl WuDunn.
