Board's second interest-rate cut in three weeks spread further
through financial markets Friday, as stock prices registered strong
gains in heavy trading and bond yields fell. By the close of
trading, the Dow Jones industrial average, which soared more than
330 points Thursday, advanced another 117.40, or 1.41 percent, to
8,416.76. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
