</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Duke, N.C. State head off for rivalry match
 &HT;    By Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DUKE VS. N.C. STATE
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, noon, Carter-Finley Stadium, Raleigh, N.C.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Duke leads 39-29-5.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Duke 3-3, 1-3 ACC; N.C. State 3-2, 1-1 ACC.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: The Blue Devils snapped their 21-game ACC losing
streak last week with a 19-16 victory over Wake Forest. ... N.C.
State is coming off its first conference loss to Georgia Tech. ...
Duke PK Sims Lenhardt, who had five field goals against Wake, is
tied for second in school history with 36 field goals. ... N.C.
State has beaten Duke four years in a row and seven of the last
eight. ... Duke hasn't won at Carter-Finley Stadium since 1984.
</P>
<P>
   WAKE FOREST VS. MARYLAND
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 1 p.m., Byrd Stadium, College Park, Md.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Maryland leads 33-12-1.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Wake Forest 2-3, 1-1 ACC; Maryland 2-4, 0-3 ACC.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: Maryland is the only ACC team without a conference
win. ... Wake Forest has lost its last two games. ... Last week,
Randall Jones became the first freshman to start at quarterback for
the Terrapins. ... Wake WR Desmond Clark needs two receptions to
become the ACC's all-time leader. He has 92 catches for 2,418
yards. ... Maryland has beaten the Deacons seven of the last nine
meetings, although Wake won 35-17 last year.
</P>
<P>
   CLEMSON VS. FLORIDA STATE
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 6 p.m., Doak Campbell Stadium, Tallahassee,
Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Florida State leads 9-2.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Clemson 2-4, 1-3 ACC; Florida State 5-1, 2-1 ACC.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: FSU has won four in a row since its shocking loss to
N.C. State. Clemson is coming off its first ACC win of the season,
over Maryland. ... The Tigers hung in against FSU last year before
Peter Warrick scored three TDs in a 35-28 win by the Seminoles. ...
FSU QB Chris Weinke had a career-high 316 yards against Miami last
week. ... Clemson's three-receiver offense netted 399 yards against
Maryland.
</P>
