<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Toombs star may commit to Dogs
 &HT;    By Mark Schlabach
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATHENS, Ga. _ Georgia is expected to receive its fifth verbal
commitment, from Toombs County quarterback/defensive back Vince
Faison, widely regarded as one of the state's top-five prospects.
</P>
<P>
   Faison, a 5-foot-11, 185-pound native of Lyons, is expected to
make his commitment official at Georgia's homecoming date against
Vanderbilt in Athens today. Faison, ranked the No. 15 athlete
nationally by SuperPrep, also considered Georgia Tech, Clemson,
South Carolina and N.C. State.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Faison had more than 1,700 all-purpose yards and
scored 22 touchdowns. On defense, he had 10 interceptions,
including three returned for scores.
</P>
<P>
   Faison also is considered a top prospect in baseball and could
be a high-round pick in June's amateur draft. He hit .356 with two
homers and 19 stolen bases as a center fielder last year. Faison is
an academic full-qualifier with a 3.86 GPA and 970 score on the
SAT.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to sign with a college and wait until June to see
where I go in the draft,'' Faison said earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
   Faison would join Georgia commitments Josh Billue of
Guntersville, Ala., Robert Brannon of Charlotte, Kentrell Curry of
Stephens County and Shedrick Wynn of Lincoln County.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
