<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    South Carolina meets Arkansas for weekend football
 &HT;    By Leo Willingham
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   SOUTH CAROLINA VS. ARKANSAS
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 1 p.m., Williams-Brice Stadium, Columbia,
S.C.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Tied 3-3.
</P>
<P>
   Records: South Carolina 1-5, 0-4 SEC East; Arkansas 5-0, 2-0 SEC
West.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: South Carolina has not lost six games in a row in a
season since 1966. ... The Gamecocks have won the last two games in
the series, including 39-13 in Little Rock last year. ... Arkansas
is looking for its first 6-0 start in 10 years. ... The Razorbacks
ranks second in the SEC in scoring offense (34.8 points per game)
and scoring defense (13.8).
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE VS. EAST TENNESSEE STATE
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 2:30 p.m., Scott Field, Starkville, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   Series: First meeting.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Mississippi State 4-1, East Tennessee State 1-4.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: This is the last non-conference game of the season
for Mississippi State, which owns a half-game lead over Arkansas in
the SEC West. ... Mississippi State has won each of its four career
games against members of the Southern Conference. ... East
Tennessee State lost to Miami (Fla.) 66-17 in its previous game
against a Division I team this season.
</P>
<P>
   ALABAMA VS. EAST CAROLINA
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 3 p.m., Legion Field, Birmingham.
</P>
<P>
   Series: First meeting.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Alabama 3-2; East Carolina 4-1.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: East Carolina has won four in a row since losing its
season opener to No. 14 Virginia Tech, while Alabama has lost two
of its last three after opening 2-0. ... During the last two games,
opponents have made 13 trips inside Alabama's 20-yard line but
managed only two touchdowns and four field goals.
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA VS. AUBURN
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 3:30 p.m., Florida Field, Gainesville, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Auburn leads 39-33-2.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Florida 5-1, 3-1 SEC East; Auburn 1-5, 1-3 SEC West.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: Doug Johnson will start at quarterback for Florida
after former starter Jesse Palmer suffered a broken collarbone last
week. ... Auburn is 1-4 for the first time since 1952. ... Auburn
leads the SEC in total defense (259.6 yards allowed per game), with
Florida second (263.3).
</P>
<P>
   LSU VS. KENTUCKY
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 9 p.m., Tiger Stadium, Baton Rouge, La.
</P>
<P>
   Series: LSU leads 34-13-1.
</P>
<P>
   Records: LSU 3-2, 1-2 SEC West; Kentucky 4-2, 1-2 SEC East.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: LSU, the preseason favorite in the SEC West, needs a
victory to keep alive any hopes of claiming its first division
title. ... The LSU defense, ranked eighth in the conference,
figures to get a stiff challenge from a Kentucky offense leading
the SEC in scoring (39.8) and passing yards (426.2).
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
