<SLUG> BC-RAC-SOLIS-LADNA-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THREE WINNERS FOR SOLIS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GREG CHRISTENSEN  
 c.1998 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA, Calif. _ Alex Solis rode three winners in a day for the
second time this week at Santa Anita Friday, and he completed his
latest triple by rallying Tomorrows Sunshine in the stretch of the
$72,000 Cascapedia.
</P>
<P>
   The victory in the 6 1/2-furlong test snapped a five-race
drought for Tomorrows Sunshine, which hadn't won since April.
</P>
<P>
   ``She has been a good horse until the last few races,'' said
Solis of the four-year-old filly, which has seven wins in 25
starts.
</P>
<P>
   Solis said the pre-race strategy devised by trainer John Sadler
was simple.
</P>
<P>
   ``He said `just ride her like you used to,' '' said Solis.
</P>
<P>
   That meant letting Tomorrows Sunshine drop off the pace and
``make one big move.''
</P>
<P>
   And Tomorrows Sunshine did just that, running fourth in the
five-horse field virtually the entire race.
</P>
<P>
   Second choice Fontal (2-1) and 6-5 favorite Career Collection
ran 1-2 most of the way, but Tomorrows Sunshine breezed by as
Fontal dropped to third and Career Collection faded to fifth.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was afraid of Fontal, I thought she might be the only
speed,'' said Solis. ``But I waited and waited and (when) thought I
had a chance to win, they were stopping.''
</P>
<P>
   Tomorrows Sunshine paid $9.00, 4.40 and 2.80. Fleeting Image
paid 5.20 and 2.80, and Fontal paid 2.40 to show.
</P>
<P>
   Solis' three wins moved him into a tie with with Laffit Pincay
Jr. for the Oak Tree riding lead (12 victories each) and he said
his stubbly beard might be here to stay a while.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to shave until 1999,'' joked Solis, who now has
2,998 career wins.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
